                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491029-name-1094" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1094" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1094" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1094" type="given" value="ALICE"></interp>ALICE MATTHEWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Richard Matthews. I was present at Marston Church, on 29th May, 1845, when the prisoner was married to Susannah Hale—I knew the prisoner before—I saw Susannah down below, about ten minutes ago.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was I sober at the time? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; very tipsy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491029-name-1095" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1095" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1095" type="surname" value="WAKEFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1095" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED WAKEFIELD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>). I produce two certificates, one I got from Waterloo Church, Lambeth, and the—other from the Parish Church of Marston, near Oxford—I compared them with the original; they are correct copies (<hi rend="italic">read</hi>)—I took the prisoner in custody at the Elephant and Castle, and on the way to the station he asked me what I took him for—I told him, and he asked who the female was, walking on a-head—I said I did not know—he said,"That is my wife, I believe"—I said I did not know her—we passed her, and he said, "That is my wife"—I said, "Your married wife?"—he said, "Yes;" and said he had been married twice—I have seen the same woman here to-day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I said I had some knowledge of her, but I did not acknowledge her to be my wife.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491029-name-1096" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491029-name-1096" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
